      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A major counter-argument is that heavy-handed regulation could stifle innovation and hinder the massive economic and social benefits AI promises. Critics argue that overly restrictive rules might inadvertently push development underground or slow down the creation of beneficial technologies. Furthermore, some believe a purely technical focus on existential risk over-hypothesizes a timeline for dangerous AGI. Therefore, they advocate for agile, industry-led standards rather than preemptive, broad governmental controls.",
      "source": "target",
